# LF is law in this repository. The cross-language referee byte-compares
# goldens, fixtures, and canonical serializations, and scripts/*.sh must
# run as committed — so no client's core.autocrlf setting may ever rewrite
# a checkout. Text files are LF on every platform, including Windows.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalize. (The .ai icon sources contain raw \r
# bytes and git's auto-detection misreads them as text; the rest are here
# so detection never gets the chance to guess wrong.)
*.ai binary
*.bin binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.icns binary
*.pdf binary
*.wasm binary
